<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="144" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">
Originally described as a 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Heterusia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heterusia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heterusia</taxonomicName>
species by Schaus (1901), this taxon was down-ranked as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="mortipax" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" rank="species" species="mortipax">mortipax</taxonomicName>
by Parsons et al. (1999). In my view, the significantly different wing pattern in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="jamaicensis" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" rank="species" species="jamaicensis">jamaicensis</taxonomicName>
justifies 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schausâ€™">Schaus'</normalizedToken>
original species rank, but further evidence from barcoding is desirable in order to consolidate its species status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="144" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">Jamaica.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="144" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="144">
In contrast to the other taxa in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="mortipax" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" rank="species" species="mortipax">mortipax</taxonomicName>
clade, this species displays a very narrow, cream-white transversal band on the forewings. The striation on the underside of the hindwing is reduced in comparison to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="mortipax" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" rank="species" species="mortipax">mortipax</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName lsidName="acothysta" pageId="13" pageNumber="144" rank="species" species="acothysta">acothysta</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
